---
import Main from '../layouts/Main.astro'
import Hero from '../layouts/Hero.astro'
import IconTarget from '../components/icons/IconTarget.astro'
import IconFlask from '../components/icons/IconFlask.astro'
import IconStar from '../components/icons/IconStar.astro'
import IconAlertTriangle from '../components/icons/IconAlertTriangle.astro'
import IconCalendar from '../components/icons/IconCalendar.astro'
import IconDatabase from '../components/icons/IconDatabase.astro'
import IconFileText from '../components/icons/IconFileText.astro'
import IconWorkflow from '../components/icons/IconWorkflow.astro'
---

<Main title="Goals">

    <Hero title="Goals" image="/images/goals.jpeg" slot="hero">
        <p class="hero-subtitle">Building standards for zebrafish toxicology research</p>
    </Hero>

    <section class="mission">
        <div class="section-label">Our Mission</div>
        <p>The Zebrafish Atlas Phenotype Project (ZAPP) is a community driven effort focused on standardizing zebrafish toxicology data and phenotypic outcome reporting. ZAPP’s success depends on active participation from the zebrafish research and toxicology community to ensure that ZAPP remains fit for purpose, sustainable, and effective in improving the integration and reuse of toxicological and phenotypic data.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="aims">
        <div class="aims-card">
            <div class="aims-card-header">
                <div class="section-icon section-icon--teal">
                    <IconTarget />
                </div>
                <h2>What ZAPP Aims to Achieve</h2>
            </div>
            <ul>
                <li>Develop a <strong>data model</strong> and standards to report zebrafish exposure experiments and resulting phenotypes</li>
                <li>Create an <strong>annotation toolkit</strong> that enables consistent data annotation following the data model and standards. This annotation toolkit will allow standards adoption without prior knowledge of ontologies or data modeling.</li>
                <li>Build a web-based, community-curated <strong>phenotype atlas</strong> that serves as a visual reference for zebrafish phenotypes</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="workflow">
        <div class="workflow-card">
            <div class="aims-card-header">
                <div class="section-icon section-icon--teal">
                    <IconFlask />
                </div>
                <h2>ZAPP Workflow &amp; Data Pipeline</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-diagram">
                <img src="/images/goals-workflow.jpg" alt="ZAPP data workflow: zebrafish exposure data collection, toxicophenotype annotation using standards, submission to the Zebrafish Phenotype Atlas with FAIR data standards" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="deliverables">
        <div class="deliverables-card">
            <div class="aims-card-header">
                <div class="section-icon section-icon--dark">
                    <IconStar />
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Key Deliverables</h2>
                    <p class="section-subtitle">Our project focuses on three major deliverables that will transform zebrafish toxicology research</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="deliverables-body">
                <div class="deliverable">
                    <h3><span class="deliverable-icon"><IconDatabase /></span>Data Model and Standards for Toxicophenotype</h3>
                    <p>We are creating a <a href="https://linkml.io/linkml/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkML</a>-based data model, based on existing toxicological data structures to support comprehensive representation of toxicological exposures, including time course, toxicants, concentrations, fish information, and phenotypic endpoints. The LinkML schema is developed with community input across multiple toxicology use cases and designed for use across organisms. More information about the data model can be found <a href="https://github.com/zappfish/zebrafish-toxicology-atlas-schema" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a>.</p>
                    <p>In addition, we improve standards to represent all data, including (but not limited to):</p>
                    <ul class="callout-list">
                        <li>The <a href="https://github.com/obophenotype/zebrafish-phenotype-ontology" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Zebrafish Phenotype ontology</a> (ZP) — to represent zebrafish phenotypes</li>
                        <li>The <a href="https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/environmental-exposure-ontology" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Environment Exposure Ontology</a> (ECTO) — to represent exposure route terms</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="deliverable">
                    <h3><span class="deliverable-icon"><IconFileText /></span>Annotation Toolkit for Toxicophenotype</h3>
                    <p>We aim to develop a community-driven toxicophenotype annotation toolkit aligned with the toxicophenotype data model to support standardized data annotation and submission to the ZAPP Atlas.</p>
                    <p>Tutorials and curation guidelines will be provided to ensure consistent annotation across contributors</p>
                </div>

                <div class="deliverable">
                    <h3><span class="deliverable-icon"><IconWorkflow /></span>Phenotype Atlas Web application</h3>
                    <p>We will collect images and metadata of morphological phenotypes from toxicology studies using the toxicophenotype annotation toolkit. These data will instantiate a zebrafish phenotype atlas and provide visual standards for comparing phenotype variation across laboratories.</p>
                    <p>The open source web-based phenotype atlas will support exploration and querying of exposures and phenotypes, display representative images and link to relevant external resources</p>
                    <p>FAIR API access to the data will be provided for third-party resources</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="action-cards">
        <div class="action-card">
            <div class="action-card-icon">
                <IconAlertTriangle />
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Contribute Data</h3>
                <p>Submit your zebrafish toxicology data and phenotype observations to help build the atlas.</p>
                <a href="/get-involved/" class="action-link">Get Involved &rsaquo;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="action-card">
            <div class="action-card-icon">
                <IconCalendar />
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3>Upcoming Workshops</h3>
                <p>Join our workshops to learn about data annotation standards and contribute to the community.</p>
                <a href="/events/" class="action-link">View Workshops &rsaquo;</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

</Main>

<style>
    .hero-subtitle { color: var(--color-text-white); margin: 0; opacity: 0.92; }

    .mission { padding-top: var(--space-8); }

    .section-label {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: var(--space-3);
        font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.1em;
        color: var(--color-text-muted);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    }
    .section-label::before {
        content: '';
        display: block;
        width: 28px;
        height: 2px;
        background: var(--color-accent);
        flex-shrink: 0;
    }

    .section-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-4); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); }
    .section-header h2, .section-header > div h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }
    .section-subtitle { font-size: var(--font-size-base); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin: 0; }

    .section-icon {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 40px;
        height: 40px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        color: #fff;
    }
    .section-icon :global(svg) { width: 20px; height: 20px; color: #fff; }
    .section-icon--green { background: var(--color-accent); }
    .section-icon--teal  { background: var(--color-primary-dark); }
    .section-icon--dark  { background: var(--color-primary); }

    .aims-card {
        background: var(--color-bg-surface);
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
        overflow: hidden;
    }
    .aims-card-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: var(--space-4);
        padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(42, 157, 138, 0.12) 0%, rgba(26, 83, 92, 0.08) 100%);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }
    .aims-card-header h2 { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .aims-card-header .section-subtitle { margin-top: var(--space-1); }
    .aims-card-header .section-icon { width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 6px; }
    .aims-card-header .section-icon :global(svg) { width: 14px; height: 14px; }
    .aims-card ul { padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-8) var(--space-8) var(--space-12); margin-bottom: 0; }
    .aims-card li { font-size: var(--font-size-body); line-height: var(--line-height-base); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
    .aims-card li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .workflow-card {
        background: var(--color-bg-surface);
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
        overflow: hidden;
    }
    .workflow-diagram { padding: var(--space-6); background: var(--color-bg-white); }
    .workflow-diagram img { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }

    .deliverables-card {
        background: var(--color-bg-surface);
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
        overflow: hidden;
    }
    .deliverables-body { padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-12); }
    .deliverable { margin-bottom: var(--space-4); padding-bottom: var(--space-4); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
    .deliverable:last-child { border-bottom: none; margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; }
    .deliverable h3 { font-size: var(--font-size-h3); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-3); }
    .deliverable-icon {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 32px;
        height: 32px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(42,157,138,0.15) 0%, rgba(26,83,92,0.10) 100%);
        border: 1px solid rgba(42,157,138,0.25);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        color: var(--color-accent);
    }
    .deliverable-icon :global(svg) { width: 16px; height: 16px; }

    .callout-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-top: var(--space-3); }
    .callout-list li {
        position: relative;
        padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4) var(--space-2) calc(var(--space-4) + 1.5rem);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
        font-size: var(--font-size-body);
        line-height: var(--line-height-base);
        background: var(--color-bg-surface);
        border-radius: 4px;
    }
    .callout-list li::before {
        content: '✓';
        position: absolute;
        left: var(--space-4);
        top: var(--space-2);
        color: var(--color-accent);
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
        line-height: var(--line-height-base);
    }
    .callout-list li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .callout-list a {
        text-decoration: none !important;
        color: var(--color-primary);
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
        transition: color 0.2s ease;
    }
    .callout-list a:hover {
        color: var(--color-primary-dark);
    }

    .action-cards { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-6); }
    .action-card {
        background: var(--color-bg-surface);
        border-radius: 10px;
        padding: var(--space-8);
        box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.10);
        display: flex;
        gap: var(--space-4);
        align-items: flex-start;
    }
    .action-card-icon {
        flex-shrink: 0;
        width: 36px;
        height: 36px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        background: var(--color-bg-base);
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        color: var(--color-primary);
    }
    .action-card-icon svg { width: 18px; height: 18px; }
    .action-card h3 { font-size: var(--font-size-h3); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
    .action-card p { font-size: var(--font-size-base); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); line-height: var(--line-height-base); }
    .action-link { font-size: var(--font-size-base); font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold); color: var(--color-accent); text-decoration: none; }
    .action-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .cta-band {
        background: var(--color-primary-dark);
        text-align: center;
        padding: var(--space-16) var(--space-8);
        border-radius: 12px;
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    .cta-band h2 { color: var(--color-text-white); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
    .cta-band p { color: var(--color-white-65); max-width: 540px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-8); }

    .cta-btn {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-8);
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--color-text-white);
        border: 2px solid var(--color-text-white);
        border-radius: 4px;
        font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
        font-size: var(--font-size-base);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
    }
    .cta-btn:hover { background: var(--color-text-white); color: var(--color-primary-dark); }

    @media (max-width: 768px) { .action-cards { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
